  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd  \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd \u2013 \u0b85\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd- \u0baa\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Soldiers remove tents - destroy them - BBC",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "We went to the area in front of the Sri Lankan President's office when we learned that the soldiers might launch an attack on the demonstrators.",
        "Within minutes, hundreds of armed soldiers and police commandos with riot gear descended from two directions, their faces covered.",
        "The security forces moved forward and became aggressive as the activists protested their presence there.",
        "Within a couple of seconds we saw the soldiers screeching away the tents and demolishing the makeshift tents and other items found on the pavements in the area.",
        "A large number of soldiers also entered the office which was besieged and entered by a large number of people last week.",
        "The soldiers pushed the demonstrators into the protest area and set up barricades to prevent them from entering.",
        "While we were returning from the area, a person who was seen with the soldiers \u2013 in civilian clothes, shouted at my colleague and told him to delete the videos from his mobile phone. Within a couple of seconds, he attacked my friend and took away his mobile phone.",
        "Even though we told them that we journalists are doing our duty, they are not ready to listen to it. They further assaulted my colleague to which we strongly objected.",
        "Another BBC reporter's microphone was snatched away and the mobile phone was returned after removing the footage, and an army officer intervened and allowed us to leave.",
        "We tried to get a response from the police and army about the attack but no one answered our phone calls \u2013 the state of emergency declared last week is still in force."
      ],
